oai_dc:dc.dc:title: University of Denver Alumni House
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: college campuses
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Exterior view of the University of Denver alumni house in Denver, Colorado, Francis Van Derber, former president of Kappa Sigma, and Roudolph McDonough, Director of Alumni Relations, stand together on the yard.

Written on back of photographic print: ''L to R Francis Van Derber, Roudolph McDonough Director, Alumni Relations. This house was alumni house at the time. Van was there because this was once the Kappa Sigma House. Later [illegible] stood by Gamma Phi Beta House. At this time the Dept. of Development was on 2nd floor. Also [illegible] news service on 2nd fl. Van had been president of Kappa Sigma locally, nationally. He paid for remodelling of alumni quarters of this house. It was called the VanDerber Alumni House as a result. ''2211 S. Josephin'' Stamped on back of photographic print: ''University of Denver Archives.''
